> This Beef Tikka Pulao is bursting full of flavours and makes the perfect dinner night option from HelloFresh. Cook up a fresh start!

Boil a full #kettle{}.

Pour the boiled water into a large #saucepan{} with @salt{1/4%tsp} on high heat. Add the
@basmati rice{150%g} and cook for ~{10-12%minutes}.

Once cooked, drain in a #sieve{} and pop back in the pan. Leave to the side until
ready to use.

Meanwhile, peel and grate the @garlic{2%cloves}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic
press{}).

Halve, peel and chop the @red onion{1%large}(peeled and chopped) into small pieces.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Once the oil is hot, add the @British beef mince{240%g} and onion. Cook until
browned and softened, ~{5-6%minutes}.

Use a #spoon{} to break up the mince as it cooks.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw mince. The mince is
> cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Once browned, drain and discard any excess fat from the beef. Season with @salt{}
and @ground black pepper{}.

Stir in the garlic and @tikka masala paste{75%g}. Cook for ~{1%minute} more.

Add the cooked rice, @beef stock paste{10%g}, @red pepper chilli jam{25%g} and
@peas{120%g} to the beef mince.

Stir together until thoroughly combined. Taste and season with salt and pepper if
needed.

Share the beef tikka pulao between your #bowls{}.

Finish with a dollop of @Greek style natural yoghurt{75%g} on top.

Enjoy!